metadata.name: Negative Space #280
metadata.description:
In this piece, special attention is paid to negative space, which is emphasized by simple / bold color palettes.

6 different styles
- Network
- Parachutes
- Flow
- Limbs
- Arcs
- Florals

9 different color palettes
- dark
- light
- yellow
- blue
- red
- green
- blue and yellow
- red and blue
- multi

Press any key to download a hi-res png.

p5.js script with a custom shader. Depending on the settings, it take some time to fully render / draw.

metadata.name: 0xSiebe #14
metadata.description: 0xSiebe is a series exploring gradients, layers and grids. It builds on my ever evolving grid framework and it is my first collection that makes use of shaders. Inspiration I got from artists like Martin Grasser and from my general fascination of light and soft colors.

metadata.name: Ignorance is Bliss #81
metadata.description:
"Ignorance is Bliss" is the second collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

People often argue over things that are not under their control. But why bother? At the end of the day, your opinion won't change anything unless you have the power to accomplish that change. Of course you can say that you are aguing for "The Truth" or "Justice", but what's the point in your bickering if you aren't going to accomplish anything?
But you can go even further than that, you can choose to ignore global problems completely, live in your own world. One who doesn't know of a problem shan't worry about it - thus, ignorance is bliss. 
Is it right or is it wrong? What's the point in arguing over what I wrote if you won't change anything? All you can do is decide for yourself.

metadata.name: Zometric #40
metadata.description:
A journey into geometric shapes.
Real art is not hidden behind complicated and obscure forms. In this collection, we have tried to achieve a unique visual clarity by using the basic visual elements. A pure mixture between piet mondrian and paul klee. A combination of visual language of classical and modern art movements. Over 15 000 combination can be generated.
Made in p5.js

metadata.name: Shredded Memories #28
metadata.description:
"Shredded Memories" is the first collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

Could we perfectly reconstruct something from shards? Perfectly recollect an event, that happened in the past, even to the tiny details? No. We will always try and fill in the empty spaces using our imagination. Not a single person has the same memory as you, everybody remembers differently.
The question is - how do you figure out which one is true?

metadata.name: reborn #122
metadata.description:
This is an album of cities too ideal to ever materialise.

It consists of 256 algorithmically generated plans that resemble drawings of Vincenzo Scamozzi, Pietro Cataneo, Filarete and other theorists of the Italian Renaissance. The cities differ in size, the grid of the streets, the landscape around them and the people that inhabit their utopian walls. They carry names that are Italian exonyms of real European cities, drawing a vision of a different world that enacts a mixture of military perfection with social superiority. Flawless, harmonious, unconquerable and utterly impossible.

History brought us many theories about ideal cities, but very few examples exist today. Italian Palmanova or Polish Zamość are the few to remind us how hard it is to shape reality according to ideals. When confronted with the material world, its idealism becomes the city's grates foe.

To zoom, press a mouse button over the image or touch the screen. To pan, keep the mouse pressed and move it around.

metadata.name: pendula #44
metadata.description: A grid of 17x17 chaotic pendulums. Each pendulum consists of 17 layers, each following a different, randomly generated square shaped route. We draw different shapes and colors at the end of each pendulum, as all 17 layers do a full lap simultaneously.

metadata.name: In the woods : natural edition. #15
metadata.description:
Project born after an inspirational walk in the woods.

This project includes different features depending on the style of the display, the size of the elements, the colors… some items are rare…

In Open Live window, press « p » to pause the building process, press « s » to save the current image.
To get a High Resolution Image : press « r » to change the resolution for high definition, the image will reload and you can then use « s » to save the image.

Visit https://sites.google.com/view/tidally-disrupted-star/ for  both genesis description of the project and an overview of the minting possibilities…

metadata.name: In the woods : close-up #21
metadata.description:
Part of the « In the woods » collection, this project was born after an inspirational walk in the woods.

This project includes different features depending on the size of the elements, the number and colors used, the different shapes, the ambient light… 

Please note that the preview image is a little bit more saturated than the real token.

In Open Live window, press « s » to save the current image.
To get a High Resolution Image : press « r » to change the resolution for high definition, the image will reload and you can then use « s » to save the image (you can change DP in the URL to  a greater value for an even larger resolution).

Visit https://sites.google.com/view/tidally-disrupted-star/ for the genesis description of the "In the woods" collection.

The first drop of this collection is still available : https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/5574

All remaining editions will be burned after a short period of time.

Twitter: @TidallyD
